### Context
#### $(\infty,1)$-Category theory
+-- {: .hide}
[[!include quasi-category theory contents]]
=--
=--
=--

Entries on the [[HomePage|nLab]] that use the **implicit $\infty$-category theory convention** leave the â€œ$\infty$â€ symbol notationally implicit when working in [[(âˆž,1)-category theory]].

In this convention

* _category_ means _[[(âˆž,1)-category]]_, and so $Cat$ means _[[(âˆž,1)Cat]]_

* _topos_ means _[[(âˆž,1)-topos]]_, and so $Topos$ means _[[(âˆž,1)Topos]]_

* _groupoid_ means _[[âˆž-groupoid]]_, and so $Gpd$ means _[[âˆžGpd]]_

* _$n$-category_ means _[[(âˆž,n)-category]]_

* _functor_ means _[[(âˆž,1)-functor]]_ or _[[(âˆž,n)-functor]]_ for some $n \in \mathbb{N}$, depending on the codomain;

* _presheaf_ means _[[(âˆž,1)-presheaf]]_, 

* _sheaf_ means _[[(âˆž,1)-sheaf]]_ , a.k.a. _[[âˆž-stack]]_   

* _limit_ means _[[(âˆž,1)-limit]]_

* _algebraic theory_ means _[[(âˆž,1)-algebraic theory]]_

* _algebra over an algebraic theory_ means _[[âˆž-algebra over an (âˆž,1)-algebraic theory]]_ .

Etc.

Note that this convention does *not* apply to the *names* of pages; see [Naming conventions](/nlab/show/HowTo#naming).  That also means that when writing pages using this convention, one must be sure to use the appropriate "pipelinks," such as `[[(infinity,1)-topos|topos]]`.


